                                                   Security expert for Chennai tie
            OUR CORRESPONDENT                      
	Mumbai: The Tamil Nadu Tennis Association has engaged the services of former CBI director R.K. Raghavan in its efforts to implement foolproof security measures for the upcoming Davis Cup tie against Australia in Chennai.         
	We have sought the help of R.K. Raghavan for the Davis Cup tie, TNTA secretary M.P. Shankar told The Telegraph on Monday.         
	The Asia-Oceania Group 1 third round tie, to be held at the Nungambakkam stadium from May 8-10, has come under scrutiny after Tennis Australia wrote to the International Tennis Federation expressing concern over visiting India following the attack on Sri Lanka cricketers in Lahore on March 3.                                                                                                                       
